fst <- read.table("FST_Analysis.txt", header=TRUE)
newfst <-as.data.frame(fst)


 ggplot(newfst, aes(x=WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST)) +
    geom_density(fill="#69b3a2", color="#e9ecef", alpha=0.8) +
    xlim(-0.05, 0.2)
## Warning: Removed 199 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density).

#Density Plot by Chromosome Arms
#Chrom2L
Chrom2L <- newfst[newfst$CHROM == "2L",]

 
 ggplot(Chrom2L, aes(x=WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST)) +
    geom_density(fill="darkmagenta", color="#e9ecef", alpha=0.8)+ xlim(-0.05, 0.15)
## Warning: Removed 91 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density).

#Fst Class Histograms

#Create Classes 
#-0.05 to 0.05
names(newfst)
## [1] "WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST" "CHROM"                  "POS"
littlegd <- newfst[newfst$WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST <= 0.05,]

nrow(littlegd)
## [1] 159621
#0.05-0.15
modgd <- newfst[newfst$WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST >= 0.05 & newfst$WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST <=0.15,]

nrow(modgd)
## [1] 7404
#0.15-0.25
greatgd <- newfst[newfst$WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST >= 0.15 & newfst$WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST <=0.25,]

nrow(greatgd)
## [1] 374
#>0.25 
verygreatgd <- newfst[newfst$WEIR_AND_COCKERHAM_FST >= 0.25,]

nrow(verygreatgd)
## [1] 30
FstClasses <- data.frame("Classes"=c("0.05-0.15", "0.15-0.25", ">0.25"),
"# Fst Values"=c(7404,374,30))   
names(FstClasses)
## [1] "Classes"       "X..Fst.Values"
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(data=FstClasses, aes(x=Classes, y=X..Fst.Values)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", fill="steelblue")+
  geom_text(aes(label=c(7404,374,30)), vjust=-0.3, size=3.5)+
  theme_minimal()
